title: The True Cost of Wellesley College: A Millionaire’s Investment Advice
subtitle: Discover how investing in a brokerage account can provide a better financial outcome for your child's future compared to traditional education costs.
content:
The True Cost of Wellesley College: A Millionaire’s Investment Advice

Did you know that Wellesley costs $90,000 a year right now? Hey, if you just want your kid to be rich, vest that $360,000 in a brokerage account for them up front and my God, they'll be a millionaire in 10 years.

And that's about as close as they're ever gonna get to being a millionaire with that liberal arts degree. I'm allowed to say that. English major, baby.
